# 080 — Security

## Code execution

- `eval` is forbidden everywhere.
- `new Function` is forbidden everywhere.
- No dynamic `require` or `import()` of user-supplied strings.
- Conditions in graph definitions are named strings resolved by `ConditionRegistry` — never evaluated as code.

## Secrets

- No secrets, API keys, or credentials in source code, graph definitions, prompts, artifacts, or logs.
- Secrets are injected via environment variables only.
- `.env` files are gitignored.

## Tool permissions

- Every tool must declare its required permissions in its definition.
- Tools requesting sensitive permissions (file write, network, external API) require explicit allow-listing.

## Human approval

- Any action classified as sensitive (data deletion, external publish, financial, legal) must go through an approval gate.
- Agents cannot approve their own outputs.

## Logging

- Logs must never contain PII, secrets, or full LLM prompt/completion payloads.
- Audit events are emitted for: run created, node executed, approval requested, approval granted/rejected, artifact written.

## Prompt injection

- LLM inputs must be sanitized before sending to `llm-gateway`.
- User-supplied content must be clearly delimited from system instructions in prompts.